      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TISSEYRE (5) finds the right race third up from a spell. The fresh run at Geelong was good before tackling a stronger maiden last time at Sandown Lakeside, not far away in fifth on that occasion. She gets the right run up to 1600m now and can break through. AUTUMN DIAMONDS (1) ran a good race first up here over this trip when sticking on for third. Any improvement off that run sees her right in the finish. RANSELOT (4) resumes as a 13-start maiden. She'll be better over further but this is a nice kick-off point in a fairly thin race. ZEYNO (7) is a filly by Pierro on debut for the Sandhu yard. Jump outs have been just fair but she can run well. KADDARI (3) could sneak into the money.",
